\s1 Historical Books
\p The books in this section describe important events in Israel's history. It begins with descriptions of how the people entered Canaan, the land which God promised to Abraham and Sarah and their descendants, and goes on to describe the time of Israel's great kings (Saul, David, and Solomon) and the division of Israel into two kingdoms (Israel in the north and Yudah in the south) who often found themselves in conflict.
